## Step 5: Re-Evaluation Scheduled Function

Create `supabase/functions/re-evaluate-held-articles/index.ts`:

```typescript
Deno.serve(async () => {
  const now = new Date();

  // Fetch all held articles whose re_evaluate_at has passed
  const { data: dueArticles } = await supabase
    .from('held_articles')
    .select('*, articles(*)')
    .eq('status', 'held')
    .lte('re_evaluate_at', now.toISOString());

  if (!dueArticles || dueArticles.length === 0) {
    return new Response(JSON.stringify({ released: 0 }), { status: 200 });
  }

  let released = 0;
  for (const held of dueArticles) {
    // Re-check: is the game still in progress?
    const gameWindow = await getActiveGameWindow(supabase, held.team_id);
    if (gameWindow) {
      // Game still active — extend hold by 1 hour
      await supabase
        .from('held_articles')
        .update({ re_evaluate_at: new Date(now.getTime() + 60 * 60 * 1000).toISOString() })
        .eq('id', held.id);
      continue;
    }

    // Game over — release article back into active pool
    await supabase
      .from('held_articles')
      .update({ status: 'released' })
      .eq('id', held.id);

    await supabase
      .from('articles')
      .update({ status: 'active', hold_reason: null })
      .eq('id', held.article_id);

    released++;
  }

  return new Response(JSON.stringify({ released, total: dueArticles.length }), { status: 200 });
});
```

Schedule this function via a Supabase cron job (pg_cron) to run every 30 minutes:
```sql
