## Step 2: Implement `detectSeasonalMode()`

Use hardcoded but configurable date ranges (stored as env vars or a config object) to determine the current phase. Fall back to `offseason` if no range matches.

```typescript
export function detectSeasonalMode(now: Date = new Date()): NFLSeasonPhase {
  const month = now.getMonth() + 1; // 1-indexed
  const day = now.getDate();

  // Super Bowl week: typically first or second week of February
  // Approximate: Feb 1–14
  if (month === 2 && day >= 1 && day <= 14) return 'super_bowl_week';

  // Playoffs: mid-January through end of January + early Feb
  if ((month === 1 && day >= 11) || (month === 2 && day < 1)) return 'playoffs';

  // Draft period: late April through early May (NFL Draft ~last week of April)
  if ((month === 4 && day >= 20) || (month === 5 && day <= 10)) return 'draft_period';

  // Preseason: August through early September
  if (month === 8 || (month === 9 && day <= 5)) return 'preseason';

  // Regular season: early September through early January
  if ((month === 9 && day > 5) || month === 10 || month === 11 || month === 12 || (month === 1 && day <= 10)) return 'regular_season';

  // Offseason: everything else (Feb 15 – late April, May 11 – July 31)
  return 'offseason';
}
```

> **Note:** Allow these date boundaries to be overridden via Supabase environment variables (e.g. `SEASON_PHASE_OVERRIDE`) so admins can manually force a phase during edge cases (e.g., a delayed Super Bowl).

