## Step 3: Web Search Verification (Optional, Stat-Named Only)

Only perform a web search if the stat contains a named/specific numeric claim (e.g., "Patrick Mahomes has 47 career touchdown passes in playoff games"):

```typescript
async function verifyStatWithWebSearch(stat: string, teamName: string): Promise<string> {
  // Heuristic: only search if stat contains digits (specific numeric claim)
  if (!/\d/.test(stat)) {
    return 'No web verification performed (no specific numeric claim detected).';
  }

  try {
    // Use your existing web search utility (e.g., Brave Search API or similar)
    const searchQuery = `${teamName} ${stat}`;
    const searchResult = await performWebSearch(searchQuery); // existing helper

    if (!searchResult || !searchResult.snippet) {
      return `Web search performed for: "${searchQuery}". No corroborating result found.`;
    }

    return `Web search query: "${searchQuery}". Result: "${searchResult.snippet}" (Source: ${searchResult.url}).`;
  } catch (err) {
    return `Web search attempted but failed: ${(err as Error).message}`;
  }
}
```

